# Minimal TahtLang Example
# A simple kingdom management game

# Settings
Game Settings (settings:main)

# Counters (hitting 0 or 100 ends the game)
Treasury (counter:treasury, killer)
Army (counter:army, killer)
People (counter:people, killer)
Church (counter:church, killer)

# Flags
Game Start (flag:start)
War Active (flag:war)

# Characters
Advisor (character:advisor)
General (character:general)
Priest (character:priest)
Merchant (character:merchant)

# Cards

Welcome (card:welcome)
    bearer: character:advisor
    weight: 100
    require: flag:start
    lockturn: dispose
    > Welcome to your kingdom, Your Majesty. Your reign begins now.
    * I am ready: -flag:start, card:_first_decision

First Decision (card:_first_decision, ring)
    bearer: character:advisor
    > Your treasury needs attention. What shall we do?
    * Raise taxes: counter:treasury 20, counter:people -10
    * Cut spending: counter:treasury 10, counter:army -10

Tax Proposal (card:tax-proposal)
    bearer: character:merchant
    weight: 1.0
    weight: 2.0 when counter:treasury < 30
    lockturn: 10
    > The merchants request lower taxes, Your Majesty.
    * Lower taxes: counter:treasury -15, counter:people 10
    * Keep current rates: counter:people -5

Military Request (card:military-request)
    bearer: character:general
    weight: 1.0
    lockturn: 8
    > We need more soldiers, Your Majesty.
    * Recruit more: counter:army 15, counter:treasury -20
    * The army is sufficient: counter:army -5

Church Donation (card:church-donation)
    bearer: character:priest
    weight: 1.0
    lockturn: 12
    > The church asks for your generous donation.
    * Donate generously: counter:church 20, counter:treasury -25
    * A modest gift: counter:church 5, counter:treasury -5
    * Decline: counter:church -15

War Declaration (card:war-declaration)
    bearer: character:general
    weight: 0.5
    require: !flag:war, counter:army > 40
    lockturn: 30
    > A neighboring kingdom threatens our borders!
    * Prepare for war: +flag:war, counter:army -10, card:_war_battle@5
    * Seek peace: counter:treasury -30, counter:people 10

War Battle (card:_war_battle, ring)
    bearer: character:general
    require: flag:war
    > The battle rages on. What are your orders?
    * Attack: counter:army -20?-10, [card:_war_victory, card:_war_defeat]
    * Defend: counter:army -10, card:_war_stalemate

War Victory (card:_war_victory, ring)
    bearer: character:general
    require: counter:army > 30
    > We have won! The enemy retreats!
    * Celebrate: -flag:war, counter:people 20, counter:treasury 30

War Defeat (card:_war_defeat, ring)
    bearer: character:general
    require: counter:army <= 30
    > We have lost the battle...
    * Retreat: -flag:war, counter:army -20, counter:people -15

War Stalemate (card:_war_stalemate, ring)
    bearer: character:general
    > Neither side gains ground.
    * Continue fighting: card:_war_battle@3
    * Negotiate peace: -flag:war, counter:treasury -20
